els10_27hwUpLink.name: els10_27hwUpLink
els10_27hwUpLink.description: Specifies whether the Up-Link I/O module is existed

els10_27hwUpLinkManufData.name: els10_27hwUpLinkManufData
els10_27hwUpLinkManufData.description: This is a 32-byte array which contains the part number, serial number, and hardware revision level of the Up-Link I/O module. This array is valid only when the els10-27hwUplink is true. If els10-27hwUplink is false, it returns an error

els10_27swdisDesc.name: els10_27swdisDesc
els10_27swdisDesc.description: The description (0-32 bytes) of the software set currently being downloaded, or a description of the software set last downloaded since the els10-27 booted.

els10_27swdisAccess.name: els10_27swdisAccess
els10_27swdisAccess.description: The version of software that may be downloaded. Attempts to download other versions of software will be rejected. The value for swdisAccess is embedded within the software files that are to be distributed via TFTP. Its value may be derived from the names of the software files. the NMS operator may wish to use the following special values: protected (1) No software downloads will be accepted any-software (2) A software download of any version of new software will be accepted - this is the factory default

els10_27swdisWriteStatus.name: els10_27swdisWriteStatus
els10_27swdisWriteStatus.description: The status of the erase/write operation.

els10_27swdisConfigIp.name: els10_27swdisConfigIp
els10_27swdisConfigIp.description: The IP address of the NMS (i.e., any IP host) that is allowed to use TFTP to send/retrieve the configuration file of the els10-27. A value of 0.0.0.0 (which is the factory specified default) prevents any NMS from obtaining access, while a value of 255.255.255.255 gives every NMS permission.

els10_27swdisConfigRetryTime.name: els10_27swdisConfigRetryTime
els10_27swdisConfigRetryTime.description: The number of seconds that the els10-27 will wait for an acknowledgment before it retransmits an unacknowledged TFTP data block. The factory specified default is 5 seconds.

els10_27swdisConfigTotalTimeout.name: els10_27swdisConfigTotalTimeout
els10_27swdisConfigTotalTimeout.description: The number of seconds that the els10-27 will wait for an acknowledgment to a data block before it cancels a TFTP session. The factory specified default is 25 seconds.

els10_27protoTable.name: els10_27protoTable
els10_27protoTable.description: This table contains configuration information specify- ing the types of protocols used to bridge, route, translate, and filter frames for each port.

els10_27protoEntry.name: els10_27protoEntry
els10_27protoEntry.description: Each entry in this table specifies which protocols are used by a particular port in the ES/1.

els10_27protoIfIndex.name: els10_27protoIfIndex
els10_27protoIfIndex.description: Identifies the interface (port) to which this entry's information belongs. The value of this variable corresponds to ifIndex, as well as most of the other port identification values in related MIBs.

els10_27protoBridge.name: els10_27protoBridge
els10_27protoBridge.description: Defines the bridging method to be applied to frames received at, or destined for, this port. Ethernet and FDDI ports may be configured for transparent, srt, or none. Token Ring ports may be configured for any of the four options. The UART may only be configured to none.

els10_27protoSuppressBpdu.name: els10_27protoSuppressBpdu
els10_27protoSuppressBpdu.description: Allows transmission of spanning tree protocol packets to be suppressed. If normal(1), 802.1d spanning tree packets are transmitted as usual. If suppressed(2), these packets are not transmitted. This option may be needed for in- teroperability with non-802.1d spanning tree protocols (e.g., DEC LanBridge 100).

els10_27protoRipListen.name: els10_27protoRipListen
els10_27protoRipListen.description: Specifies whether the port should listen for internet Routing Information Protocol (RFC-1058) packets, in order to build the routing table for the unit.

els10_27protoTrunking.name: els10_27protoTrunking
els10_27protoTrunking.description: Specifies whether SMC's trunking protocol (an extension to the standard Spanning Tree) is to be used over this port.

els10_27sprotoTransmitPacing.name: els10_27sprotoTransmitPacing
els10_27sprotoTransmitPacing.description: When enabled, introduces delays into normal transmission of frames, to reduce the probability of collisions during heavy traffic.

els10_27trunkTable.name: els10_27trunkTable
els10_27trunkTable.description: This table describes the trunking status and attributes of the interfaces that are configured for bridge trunking.

els10_27trunkEntry.name: els10_27trunkEntry
els10_27trunkEntry.description: An entry exists in this table for each physical interface (port) that is configured for trunking.

els10_27trunkIfIndex.name: els10_27trunkIfIndex
els10_27trunkIfIndex.description: Identifies a physical interface (port) which is configured for LAN trunking. The value of this variable corresponds to ifIndex, as well as most of the other port identification values in related MIBs.

els10_27trunkState.name: els10_27trunkState
els10_27trunkState.description: If off(1) then this link has not been enabled for trunking. If closed(2) then this link has not yet received any Trunking PDUs. If oneway(3) then incoming Trunking PDUs do not indicate that our PDUs are being successfully received by the far end. If joined(4) then this link is actively participating in the trunk group. If perturbed(5) then this link is actively participating in the trunk group; however, the transmission of data packets has been temporarily stopped due to a change in membership of the group. If helddown(6) then an error has been detected and the link is being held out-of-service until the error clears. If broken(7) then this link has been configured for trunking, but the port is physically non-operational.

els10_27trunkRemoteBridgeAddr.name: els10_27trunkRemoteBridgeAddr
els10_27trunkRemoteBridgeAddr.description: The MAC address portion of the bridge ID of the remote bridge.

els10_27trunkRemoteIp.name: els10_27trunkRemoteIp
els10_27trunkRemoteIp.description: The IP address of the remote bridge, as reported by that bridge for administrative purposes.

els10_27trunkLastError.name: els10_27trunkLastError
els10_27trunkLastError.description: The last reason for failure when the link is in closed, oneway, or helddown state.

els10_27trunkLinkOrdinal.name: els10_27trunkLinkOrdinal
els10_27trunkLinkOrdinal.description: The position of this link within the trunk group.

els10_27trunkLinkCount.name: els10_27trunkLinkCount
els10_27trunkLinkCount.description: The number of links within the trunk group.

els10_27trunkLastChange.name: els10_27trunkLastChange
els10_27trunkLastChange.description: The number of seconds since els10-27trunkState changed.

els10_27WorkGroupNextNumber.name: els10_27WorkGroupNextNumber
els10_27WorkGroupNextNumber.description: The next available workgroup number to be used. When creating a new workgroup, it is recommended to read the value of the variable and use it to key into the workgroup table.

els10_27WorkGroupCurrentCount.name: els10_27WorkGroupCurrentCount
els10_27WorkGroupCurrentCount.description: The total number of workgroups currently defined.

els10_27WorkGroupMaxCount.name: els10_27WorkGroupMaxCount
els10_27WorkGroupMaxCount.description: The maximum number of workgroups allowed.

els10_27WorkGroupTable.name: els10_27WorkGroupTable
els10_27WorkGroupTable.description: This table contains work group definitions for the interfaces.

els10_27WorkGroupEntry.name: els10_27WorkGroupEntry
els10_27WorkGroupEntry.description: Each entry in this table contains a definition of a work group.

els10_27WorkGroupNumber.name: els10_27WorkGroupNumber
els10_27WorkGroupNumber.description: An integer that identifies the work group, used as an index to this table.

els10_27WorkGroupPorts.name: els10_27WorkGroupPorts
els10_27WorkGroupPorts.description: A list of all ports within the group. The first octet specified ports 1-8, the second 9-16, etc.

els10_27WorkGroupType.name: els10_27WorkGroupType
els10_27WorkGroupType.description: The type of work group: all - no additional information needs to be supplied.

els10_27trapControlTable.name: els10_27trapControlTable
els10_27trapControlTable.description: This table contains information about the severity of each trap and whether the trap is currently enabled.

els10_27trapEnabled.name: els10_27trapEnabled
els10_27trapEnabled.description: Enable or disable the generation of this trap.

els10_27trapSeverity.name: els10_27trapSeverity
els10_27trapSeverity.description: A user-definable severity, indicating the importance of the trap.

els10_27trapSeverityControlTable.name: els10_27trapSeverityControlTable
els10_27trapSeverityControlTable.description: This table contains information about whether a class of traps of a particular severity are enabled or disabled.

els10_27trapSeverityControlSeverity.name: els10_27trapSeverityControlSeverity
els10_27trapSeverityControlSeverity.description: A user-definable severity, indicating the importance of the trap.

els10_27trapSeverityEnable.name: els10_27trapSeverityEnable
els10_27trapSeverityEnable.description: Enable or disable all traps of a given severity level.

els10_27trapIncludeText.name: els10_27trapIncludeText
els10_27trapIncludeText.description: Whether or not a formatted text string is included in the trap PDU.

els10_27trapTime.name: els10_27trapTime
els10_27trapTime.description: The time, in centiseconds, which should expire between the sending of traps.

els10_27trapRetry.name: els10_27trapRetry
els10_27trapRetry.description: The number of times any enterprise-specific trap is to be sent for a given event. PDUs are retried using a truncated exponential backoff: 2 seconds, 4 seoncs, 8 seconds, 16 seconds, and then 32 seconds for all succeeding intervals.

els10_27trapNumber.name: els10_27trapNumber
els10_27trapNumber.description: The number of traps that are in the els10-27trapTable.

els10_27trapTable.name: els10_27trapTable
els10_27trapTable.description: This table contains the latest traps that have been generated.

els10_27trapEntryIndex.name: els10_27trapEntryIndex
els10_27trapEntryIndex.description: A number representing the order in which the trap occurred in time. This 32 bit number can wrap.

els10_27trapEntryTimeStamp.name: els10_27trapEntryTimeStamp
els10_27trapEntryTimeStamp.description: The time at which the trap occurred.

els10_27trapEntryNumber.name: els10_27trapEntryNumber
els10_27trapEntryNumber.description: The specific trap number, as specified in the TRAP PDU.

els10_27trapEntrySeverity.name: els10_27trapEntrySeverity
els10_27trapEntrySeverity.description: A user-definable severity, indicating the importance of the trap.

els10_27pingDataTimeout.name: els10_27pingDataTimeout
els10_27pingDataTimeout.description: The time, in centiseconds, from the last ping activity (a send or receive of an ECHO_RESPONSE or ECHO_REQUEST message), to when the els10-27pingEntry information for that ping request will be deleted.

els10_27pingTable.name: els10_27pingTable
els10_27pingTable.description: The set of information describing the active ping requests and their results.

els10_27pingEntry.name: els10_27pingEntry
els10_27pingEntry.description: The parameters, state, and results of a ping request.

els10_27pingNMSAddr.name: els10_27pingNMSAddr
els10_27pingNMSAddr.description: The IP address of the NMS, used to determine which ping request to return information on.

els10_27pingDestAddr.name: els10_27pingDestAddr
els10_27pingDestAddr.description: The IP address which is to be the destination of the ping ECHO_REQUEST. This variable cannot be set while els10-27pingOperation is on.

els10_27pingState.name: els10_27pingState
els10_27pingState.description: The current state of the ping request.

els10_27pingCount.name: els10_27pingCount
els10_27pingCount.description: The number of ping requests which are to be sent. This variable cannot be set while els10-27pingOperation is on.

els10_27pingDataSize.name: els10_27pingDataSize
els10_27pingDataSize.description: The datagram packet size which will be sent with the ECHO_REQUEST, in bytes. This variable cannot be set while els10-27pingOperation is on.

els10_27pingWait.name: els10_27pingWait
els10_27pingWait.description: The time, in centiseconds, between the sending of each ECHO_REQUEST message. This variable cannot be set while els10-27pingOperation is on.

els10_27pingTimeOut.name: els10_27pingTimeOut
els10_27pingTimeOut.description: The time, in centiseconds, since the last ECHO_RESPONSE was received (or the last ECHO_REQUEST was sent, if there have been no responses) when the ping request will time out. This variable cannot be set while els10-27pingOperation is on.

els10_27pingOperation.name: els10_27pingOperation
els10_27pingOperation.description: Setting els10-27pingOperation to on will begin the ping request. Setting els10-27pingOperation to off will terminate the ping request.

els10_27pingMin.name: els10_27pingMin
els10_27pingMin.description: The minimum round trip time for the ping requests and responses, in centiseconds.

els10_27pingMax.name: els10_27pingMax
els10_27pingMax.description: The maximum round trip for the ping requests and responses, in centiseconds.

els10_27pingAvg.name: els10_27pingAvg
els10_27pingAvg.description: The average round trip time for the ping requests and responses, in centiseconds.

els10_27pingNumTransmitted.name: els10_27pingNumTransmitted
els10_27pingNumTransmitted.description: The number of ICMP ECHO_REQUEST messages that have been transmitted during this ping request.

els10_27pingNumReceived.name: els10_27pingNumReceived
els10_27pingNumReceived.description: The number of ICMP ECHO_RESPONSE messages that have been received as a result of this ping request.

els10_27traceDataTimeout.name: els10_27traceDataTimeout
els10_27traceDataTimeout.description: The time, in centiseconds, from the last traceroute activity (the response to or timeout of the last probe sent), to when the els10-27traceEntry information for that traceroute request will be deleted.

els10_27traceTable.name: els10_27traceTable
els10_27traceTable.description: The set of information describing the active traceroute requests and their results.

els10_27traceEntry.name: els10_27traceEntry
els10_27traceEntry.description: The parameters, state, and results of a traceroute request.

els10_27traceNMSAddr.name: els10_27traceNMSAddr
els10_27traceNMSAddr.description: The IP address of the NMS, used to determine which traceroute request to return information on.

els10_27traceDestAddr.name: els10_27traceDestAddr
els10_27traceDestAddr.description: The IP address which is to be the destination of the traceroute request.This variable cannot be set while els10-27traceOperation is on.

els10_27traceMaxTTL.name: els10_27traceMaxTTL
els10_27traceMaxTTL.description: The maximum time-to-live for outgoing traceroute probe packets. This determines the number of hops that can be in a traceroute. This variable cannot be set while els10-27traceOperation is on.

els10_27traceDataSize.name: els10_27traceDataSize
els10_27traceDataSize.description: The size of the datagram sent with each probe. This variable cannot be set while els10-27traceOperation is on.

els10_27traceNumProbes.name: els10_27traceNumProbes
els10_27traceNumProbes.description: The number of probes which are sent for each hop. This variable cannot be set while els10-27traceOperation is on.

els10_27traceWait.name: els10_27traceWait
els10_27traceWait.description: The time to wait in response to a probe. This variable cannot be set while els10-27traceOperation is on.

els10_27traceOperation.name: els10_27traceOperation
els10_27traceOperation.description: Setting els10-27traceOperation to on will begin the traceroute request. Setting els10-27traceOperation to off will terminate the traceroute request.

els10_27traceHop.name: els10_27traceHop
els10_27traceHop.description: The hop count for a set of probes with a particular TTL.

els10_27traceHopAddr.name: els10_27traceHopAddr
els10_27traceHopAddr.description: The IP address of the host which responded for a probe with a particular TTL.

els10_27traceProbe.name: els10_27traceProbe
els10_27traceProbe.description: The probe instance for a particular hop.

els10_27traceState.name: els10_27traceState
els10_27traceState.description: The current state of the trace probe.

els10_27traceTime.name: els10_27traceTime
els10_27traceTime.description: Round trip time of a probe for a particular hop.

els10_27volmirrorMode.name: els10_27volmirrorMode
els10_27volmirrorMode.description: To turn port mirroring on or off.

els10_27volmirrorPort.name: els10_27volmirrorPort
els10_27volmirrorPort.description: The number of the port whose data will be mirrored to a special monitor or analyzer port.

els10_27volmonitorPort.name: els10_27volmonitorPort
els10_27volmonitorPort.description: Identifies the monitor or analyzer port to receive frames from the special mirror port.

els10_27volMirrorMacTable.name: els10_27volMirrorMacTable
els10_27volMirrorMacTable.description: A table that contains information for the mirroring on MAC addresses.

els10_27volmirrorMacEntry.name: els10_27volmirrorMacEntry
els10_27volmirrorMacEntry.description: Information about specific unicast MAC addresses for which mirroring will act upon.

els10_27VlanVersionNumber.name: els10_27VlanVersionNumber
els10_27VlanVersionNumber.description: Specifies the version IEEE 802.1Q VLAN that has been implemented to.

els10_27VlanOperatingMode.name: els10_27VlanOperatingMode
els10_27VlanOperatingMode.description: Selects the mode of operation. The switch can operate as simply an 802.1d switch, or an 802.1d switch with IEEE VLAN capability (802.1Q). A read of this object will return the current operating mode.

els10_27VlanResetDefaults.name: els10_27VlanResetDefaults
els10_27VlanResetDefaults.description: To reset the specified bridge. The filtering database is cleared and initialized with the entries specified in the Permananent database, and the Bridge protocol Entity is initialized. While initializing a read will return a value of reset (2). While operational a read will return a value of operating (1).

els10_27VlanGVRPEnable.name: els10_27VlanGVRPEnable
els10_27VlanGVRPEnable.description: If the switch is operating in 802.1Q mode, this selects whether GVRP protocol messages should be processed and VLANs configured accordingly for each port on the switch. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the next octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the most significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the VLAN bridge is represented by single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'

els10_27VlanAccessList.name: els10_27VlanAccessList
els10_27VlanAccessList.description: A list of ports that should act as 'Access Ports'. These ports will strip all tags on egress and also make use of a shared database that will automatically be kept by the firmware. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the next octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the most significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the VLAN bridge is represented by single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'

els10_27VlanNumActiveEntries.name: els10_27VlanNumActiveEntries
els10_27VlanNumActiveEntries.description: The number of active VLAN entries for the device. This includes both static and dynamic VLANs.

els10_27VlanNumConfiguredEntries.name: els10_27VlanNumConfiguredEntries
els10_27VlanNumConfiguredEntries.description: The number of configured VLAN entries for the device.

els10_27VlanMaxNumEntries.name: els10_27VlanMaxNumEntries
els10_27VlanMaxNumEntries.description: The maximum number of VLAN entries for the device.

els10_27VlanConfigTable.name: els10_27VlanConfigTable
els10_27VlanConfigTable.description: This table allows for the creation, deletion, and modification of specific VLANs. The ports defined within this group will be members of the 'member set' as defined in the IEEE 802.1Q specification. Although this is configured as a table, there is only a single instance. Entries should be referenced as simple variables

els10_27VlanConfigEntry.name: els10_27VlanConfigEntry
els10_27VlanConfigEntry.description: Allows for configuration of specific VLAN entries. Although this is configured as a table, there is only a single instance. Entries should be referenced as simple variables

els10_27VlanConfigIndex.name: els10_27VlanConfigIndex
els10_27VlanConfigIndex.description: The index into the table of vlans. The table has 32 entries (0 - 31). An index value outside this range will reference the local variable. For example if the index is set to -1 and the els10-27VlanConfigVID object is read, the local variable is read, not the table entry. By using an out of range value, the local variables can be read. Only the local variables are written to until els10-27VlanConfigStatus is written.

els10_27VlanConfigVID.name: els10_27VlanConfigVID
els10_27VlanConfigVID.description: The 12 bit VLAN Identifier associated with the configured VLAN. Valid range (1..4094)

els10_27VlanConfigPorts.name: els10_27VlanConfigPorts
els10_27VlanConfigPorts.description: Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the next octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the most significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the VLAN bridge is represented by single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

els10_27VlanConfigIP.name: els10_27VlanConfigIP
els10_27VlanConfigIP.description: The IP address to be used to access the unit on this Vlan. This must be a valid host address.

els10_27VlanConfigIPMask.name: els10_27VlanConfigIPMask
els10_27VlanConfigIPMask.description: The IP subnet mask to be used with this IP address.

els10_27VlanConfigName.name: els10_27VlanConfigName
els10_27VlanConfigName.description: The ASCII name associated with this VLAN.

els10_27VlanConfigStatus.name: els10_27VlanConfigStatus
els10_27VlanConfigStatus.description: A set with any value of will create, modify or delete entries in the specified VLAN according to the vlaue in els10-27VlanConfigEstablish.

els10_27VlanConfigEstablish.name: els10_27VlanConfigEstablish
els10_27VlanConfigEstablish.description: A set of the value create(1), causes an entry to be created in the els10-27VlanConfigTable as specified by the instancing information of els10-27VlanConfigVID, els10-27VlanConfigName, and els10-27VlanConfigPorts etc, when the els10-27VlanConfigStatus is written to. A set of delete(2) causes the specified entry to be removed from the table, when the els10-27VlanConfigStatus is written to.

els10_27VlanConfigEgressTable.name: els10_27VlanConfigEgressTable
els10_27VlanConfigEgressTable.description: This table allows for the specifying of the default VLAN ID for a specific port. If NOT configured as an 'Access' port, then packets containing this VLAN ID will have the tag stripped on egress. This will set the PVID for each port contained within the list.

els10_27VlanConfigEgressEntry.name: els10_27VlanConfigEgressEntry
els10_27VlanConfigEgressEntry.description: Allows for configuration of specific Egress entries. Although this is configured as a table, there is only a single instance. Entries should be referenced as simple variables

els10_27VlanEgressIndex.name: els10_27VlanEgressIndex
els10_27VlanEgressIndex.description: The index into the Vlan table. A port must be a member of this Vlan prior to assigning this Id as the default. The table has 32 entries (0 - 31). An index value outside this range will reference the local variable. For example if the index is set to -1 and the els10-27VlanEgressVID object is read, the local variable is read, not the table entry. By using an out of range value, the local variables can be read. Only the local variables are written to until els10-27VlanEgressStatus is written.

els10_27VlanEgressVID.name: els10_27VlanEgressVID
els10_27VlanEgressVID.description: The 12 bit VLAN Identifier associated with the configured VLAN. Valid range (1..4094)

els10_27VlanEgressList.name: els10_27VlanEgressList
els10_27VlanEgressList.description: The set of ports to which traffic destined for the VLAN specified by els10-27VlanEgressVID on the device will have this tag stripped on egress. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with thee first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the most significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the VLAN bridge is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

els10_27VlanEgressStatus.name: els10_27VlanEgressStatus
els10_27VlanEgressStatus.description: A set with any value will change all associated entries in the els10-27VlanEgressList to have the default Vlan id set to the value in els10-27VlanEgressVID using the els10-27VlanEgressIndex vlaue to index into the table.

els10_27VlanFilterGVRPTable.name: els10_27VlanFilterGVRPTable
els10_27VlanFilterGVRPTable.description: This table allows for the specifying of VLAN ID's that will be resticted from being learnt by the device. If a GVRP packet is received specifying this VLAN ID, it will be ignored.

els10_27VlanFilterGVRPEntry.name: els10_27VlanFilterGVRPEntry
els10_27VlanFilterGVRPEntry.description: Allows for configuration of specific entries. Although this is configured as a table, there is only a single instance. Entries should be referenced as simple variables

els10_27VlanFilterGVRPIndex.name: els10_27VlanFilterGVRPIndex
els10_27VlanFilterGVRPIndex.description: The index into the Vlan Filter table. A maximum of 32 Vlan ID can be restricted from being learnt via GVRP. The table has 32 entries (0 - 31). An index value outside this range will reference the local variable. For example if the index is set to -1 and the els10-27VlanFilterGVRPVID object is read, the local variable is read, not the table entry. By using an out of range value, the local variables can be read. Only the local variables are written to until els10-27VlanFilterGVRPStatus is written.

els10_27VlanFilterGVRPVID.name: els10_27VlanFilterGVRPVID
els10_27VlanFilterGVRPVID.description: The 12 bit VLAN Identifier associated with the configured VLAN. Valid range (1..4094)

els10_27VlanFilterGVRPList.name: els10_27VlanFilterGVRPList
els10_27VlanFilterGVRPList.description: The set of ports that will be restricted from leaning of a VLAN ID from a GVRP message. The VLAN ID is specified by els10-27VlanFilterGVRPVID. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with thee first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the most significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the VLAN bridge is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

els10_27VlanFilterGVRPStatus.name: els10_27VlanFilterGVRPStatus
els10_27VlanFilterGVRPStatus.description: A set with any value enables all associated entries in els10-27VlanFilterGVRPVID table for the specified VLAN.

els10_27VlanFilterGVRPEstablishVID.name: els10_27VlanFilterGVRPEstablishVID
els10_27VlanFilterGVRPEstablishVID.description: A set of the value create(1), will cause an entry to be created in the els10-27VlanFilterGVRPTable using els10-27VlanFilterGVRPIndex, els10-27VlanFilterGVRpVID, and els10-27VlanFilterGVRPList once a write is done to els10-27VlanFilterGVRPStatus. A set of delete(2) causes the specified entry to be removed from the table once a write is done to els10-27VlanFilterGVRPStatus.

els10_27VlanStaticTable.name: els10_27VlanStaticTable
els10_27VlanStaticTable.description: Allows for configuration of specific VLAN/MAC Address entries and to specify the port to which traffic destined for this address pair should be forwarded. These entries will not be aged out of the forwarding data base, but they will not be saved across a reboot.

els10_27VlanStaticEntry.name: els10_27VlanStaticEntry
els10_27VlanStaticEntry.description: Allows for configuration of specific entries. Although this is configured as a table, there is only a single instance. Entries should be referenced as simple variables

els10_27VlanStaticVID.name: els10_27VlanStaticVID
els10_27VlanStaticVID.description: The 12 bit VLAN Identifier associated with the configured VLAN. Valid range (1..4094)

els10_27VlanStaticPort.name: els10_27VlanStaticPort
els10_27VlanStaticPort.description: An integer designating the port number to associate this address to.

els10_27VlanStaticEstablish.name: els10_27VlanStaticEstablish
els10_27VlanStaticEstablish.description: A set of the value create(1), causes an entry to be created as specified by the instancing information of els10-27VlanSaticVID, els10-27VlanStaticMAC, and els10-27VlanStaticPort. A set of delete(2) causes the specified entry to be removed from the table.

els10_27IPMulticastStatus.name: els10_27IPMulticastStatus
els10_27IPMulticastStatus.description: Parameter to enable or disable IP multicast filtering on the device. When enabled, the device will examine IP Multicast data packets and dynamically set up filter ports to prevent flooding. The default is disabled.

els10_27ipmInterfaceRtr.name: els10_27ipmInterfaceRtr
els10_27ipmInterfaceRtr.description: Parameter to enable or disable the inclusion of this interface in all Multicast filters. When enabled, all IP Multicast packets for all group filters will be transmitted over this interface. Value is a bit mask.

els10_27igmpStatus.name: els10_27igmpStatus
els10_27igmpStatus.description: Parameter to enable or disable IGMP snooping on the device. When enabled, the device will examine IGMP packets and set up filters for IGMP ports. The default is enabled.

els10_27igmpQueryStatus.name: els10_27igmpQueryStatus
els10_27igmpQueryStatus.description: Parameter to enable or disable the device to act as a Querier. If enabled, the device will send out a Query as a Proxy to solicit reports. The device will not become an IGMP router. The default is disabled.

els10_27igmpQueryCount.name: els10_27igmpQueryCount
els10_27igmpQueryCount.description: Maximum number of queries that have not been heard on the system before the system starts taking action to solicit reports (default is 5).

els10_27igmpPortDelay.name: els10_27igmpPortDelay
els10_27igmpPortDelay.description: Timeout value (mins) between IGMP Reports or IGMP Queries received on a port before the system times out the entry from the Multicast Address Filter (default is 5 minutes).

els10_27igmpCacheTable.name: els10_27igmpCacheTable
els10_27igmpCacheTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the IP multicast groups for which there are members on a particular interface.

els10_27igmpCacheEntry.name: els10_27igmpCacheEntry
els10_27igmpCacheEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the els10-27igmpCacheTable.

els10_27igmpCacheAddress.name: els10_27igmpCacheAddress
els10_27igmpCacheAddress.description: The IP multicast group address for which this entry contains information.

els10_27igmpCacheIfIndex.name: els10_27igmpCacheIfIndex
els10_27igmpCacheIfIndex.description: The interface for which this entry contains infor- mation for an IP multicast group address.

els10_27igmpCacheExpiryTime.name: els10_27igmpCacheExpiryTime
els10_27igmpCacheExpiryTime.description: The minimum amount of time remaining before this entry will be aged out.

els10_27FlowControlBackPressure.name: els10_27FlowControlBackPressure
els10_27FlowControlBackPressure.description: Control back pressure on a system wide basis. On (1), Off (2)

els10_27FlowControlThresholdValue.name: els10_27FlowControlThresholdValue
els10_27FlowControlThresholdValue.description: A value specified as a percent of the available buffers. When fewer than the percent of the avaialable buffers is detected, flow control will be initiated. Flow control will cease when the free buffer count meets or exceeds this percent.

els10_27FlowControlPauseInteval.name: els10_27FlowControlPauseInteval
els10_27FlowControlPauseInteval.description: A value between 10 and 65535. Each pause interval is equal to '5.12 microseconds'. A value of 10 will equal '51.2 microseconds'.

els10_27FlowControlTable.name: els10_27FlowControlTable
els10_27FlowControlTable.description: Provides a list of control objects over flow control parameters.

els10_27FlowControlEntry.name: els10_27FlowControlEntry
els10_27FlowControlEntry.description: Defines a particular entry containing objects pertaining to definition and control over flow control ports.

els10_27FlowControlInterface.name: els10_27FlowControlInterface
els10_27FlowControlInterface.description: The MIB2 interface for which this flow control information pertains

els10_27FlowControlEnable.name: els10_27FlowControlEnable
els10_27FlowControlEnable.description: Control 802.3x flow control on a per interface basis. On (1), Off (2)

els10_27FlowControlRxPauseFrames.name: els10_27FlowControlRxPauseFrames
els10_27FlowControlRxPauseFrames.description: The number of pause frames received on this interface.

els10_27FlowControlTxPauseFrames.name: els10_27FlowControlTxPauseFrames
els10_27FlowControlTxPauseFrames.description: The number of pause frames transmitted on this interface.

els10_27WriteStatusTrap.name: els10_27WriteStatusTrap
els10_27WriteStatusTrap.description: Sent when a bank of Flash EPROM has been erased. If els10-27swdisWriteStatus indicates success, then the unit is ready to be downloaded with the new software.

els10_27PortFunctionsTrap.name: els10_27PortFunctionsTrap
els10_27PortFunctionsTrap.description: Sent whenever the current functional state (active protocols) of the port has changed.

els10_27RxQueuesTrap.name: els10_27RxQueuesTrap
els10_27RxQueuesTrap.description: Sent whenever the number of times that the port's receiver has stopped receiving packets due to buffer space shortages has exceeded the port's limit.

els10_27RxStormFlagTrap.name: els10_27RxStormFlagTrap
els10_27RxStormFlagTrap.description: Sent whenever broadcast/multicast storm protection has been invoked for the port.

els10_27TxCongestsTrap.name: els10_27TxCongestsTrap
els10_27TxCongestsTrap.description: Sent whenever packets destined for the unit itself were discarded due to lack of buffer space.

els10_27DebugStringIdTrap.name: els10_27DebugStringIdTrap
els10_27DebugStringIdTrap.description: Sent whenever the unit has a debug text string to be displayed. The text strings are sent in a stream-like fashion.

els10_27LpbkOperationTrap.name: els10_27LpbkOperationTrap
els10_27LpbkOperationTrap.description: Send whenever the unit has finished a loop back test, or a loop back error has been detected.

els10_27TrunkStateTrap.name: els10_27TrunkStateTrap
els10_27TrunkStateTrap.description: A trunking state change transition has occurred. The possible transitions are: CLOSED-ONEWAY ONEWAY-PERTURBED PERTURBED-JOINED JOINED-HELDDOWN CLOSED-HELDDOWN ONEWAY-HELDDOWN PERTURBED-HELDDOWN

els10_27TrunkBridgeAddrTrap.name: els10_27TrunkBridgeAddrTrap
els10_27TrunkBridgeAddrTrap.description: The associated trunking MAC address of the bridge ID of the remote bridge has changed.

els10_27TrunkIPAddrTrap.name: els10_27TrunkIPAddrTrap
els10_27TrunkIPAddrTrap.description: The associated trunking IP address of the remote bridge has changed.

els10_27TrunkErrorTrap.name: els10_27TrunkErrorTrap
els10_27TrunkErrorTrap.description: An error has occurred in trunking.

els10_27TrunkLinkOrdinalTrap.name: els10_27TrunkLinkOrdinalTrap
els10_27TrunkLinkOrdinalTrap.description: The port's index in the trunking group has changed.

els10_27TrunkLinkCountTrap.name: els10_27TrunkLinkCountTrap
els10_27TrunkLinkCountTrap.description: The number of ports in the trunking group has changed.

els10_27DiagUnitBootedTrap.name: els10_27DiagUnitBootedTrap
els10_27DiagUnitBootedTrap.description: The unit has booted. els10-27adminFatalErr contains information about why the unit rebooted.

els10_27StorageFailureTrap.name: els10_27StorageFailureTrap
els10_27StorageFailureTrap.description: Sent if the unit's Configuration EEPROM has failed. The unit will not be able to reboot, and must be returned to the factory.

els10_27PortCongestedTrap.name: els10_27PortCongestedTrap
els10_27PortCongestedTrap.description: Sent whenever outbound congestion control has been invoked for the port.

els10_27TopChangeBegunTrap.name: els10_27TopChangeBegunTrap
els10_27TopChangeBegunTrap.description: The spanning tree topology has begun to change.

els10_27TopChangeEndTrap.name: els10_27TopChangeEndTrap
els10_27TopChangeEndTrap.description: The spanning tree topology has stopped changing.

els10_27IfErrorsTrap.name: els10_27IfErrorsTrap
els10_27IfErrorsTrap.description: Sent whenever the number of hardware errors in received and transmitted packets has exceeded the port's limit.

els10_27StRootIDTrap.name: els10_27StRootIDTrap
els10_27StRootIDTrap.description: The spanning tree root bridge ID for the unit has changed.

els10_27StRootCostTrap.name: els10_27StRootCostTrap
els10_27StRootCostTrap.description: The unit's spanning tree cost to the root bridge has changed.

els10_27StRootPortTrap.name: els10_27StRootPortTrap
els10_27StRootPortTrap.description: The unit's spanning tree root port has changed.

els10_27StMaxAgeTrap.name: els10_27StMaxAgeTrap
els10_27StMaxAgeTrap.description: The unit's spanning tree maximum age has changed.

els10_27StHelloTimeTrap.name: els10_27StHelloTimeTrap
els10_27StHelloTimeTrap.description: The unit's spanning tree hello time has changed.

els10_27StForwardDelayTrap.name: els10_27StForwardDelayTrap
els10_27StForwardDelayTrap.description: The unit's spanning tree forward delay time has changed.

els10_27StDesigRootTrap.name: els10_27StDesigRootTrap
els10_27StDesigRootTrap.description: The Root Bridge ID in received Spanning Tree Configuration BPDUs from the port has changed.

els10_27StPortDesigBridgeTrap.name: els10_27StPortDesigBridgeTrap
els10_27StPortDesigBridgeTrap.description: The bridge ID of the spanning tree designated bridge of the LAN/WAN to which the port is attached has changed.

els10_27StPortDesigCostTrap.name: els10_27StPortDesigCostTrap
els10_27StPortDesigCostTrap.description: The cost to the spanning tree root bridge from the designated port of the LAN/WAN to which the port is attached has changed.

els10_27StPortDesigPortTrap.name: els10_27StPortDesigPortTrap
els10_27StPortDesigPortTrap.description: The port ID of the spanning tree designated port of the LAN/WAN to which the port is attached has changed.

els10_27StPortStateTrap.name: els10_27StPortStateTrap
els10_27StPortStateTrap.description: The spanning tree state of the port has changed.

els10_27hwDiagTrap.name: els10_27hwDiagTrap
els10_27hwDiagTrap.description: Sent whenever the unit's diagnostics have indicated an error.

els10_27InvalidConfigurationFileTrap.name: els10_27InvalidConfigurationFileTrap
els10_27InvalidConfigurationFileTrap.description: Diagnostics has detected corrupted configuration data. Default parameter values have been restored.

els10_27StInvalidFlashCodeImageTrap.name: els10_27StInvalidFlashCodeImageTrap
els10_27StInvalidFlashCodeImageTrap.description: An invalid code image was detected in flash memory. An attempt will be made to obtain a valid image.
